===Noun===
'''eng''' (''plural'' '''engs''')

:(''orthography'') [[ŋ]]: The Latin-based letter formed by combining the letters ''n'' and ''g'', used in the [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]], [[w:Saami|Saami]], [[w:Mende|Mende]], ans some Australian aboriginal languages. In the IPA, it represents the voiced velar nasal, the ''ng'' sound in [[running|runni'''ng''']] and [[rink|ri'''n'''k]].

